title: For Sale:  Savage Arms MKII FVT - Black December Sale :-)
postcontent:
Savage Mark II FVT is a solid, dependable rimfire that's light enough to be a child's first rifle or the experienced shooters varmint/pinker gun. Savage actions are made to fire flawlessly for generations and the synthetic stock can stand up to harsh weather conditions. The Savage Accutrigger is fully adjustable and allows for a very short length of pull. The Mark II features a heavy barrel and the incredible Savage Accu-Trigger for unparalleled rimfire accuracy.



From casual plinking to serious hunting, the versatile rimfire Savage Mark II FVT Rifle can handle it all. This bolt action Mark II FVT is presented with a beautiful blued carbon steel barrel and synthetic black stock, and features AccuTrigger, peep sight, thumb safety and detachable box 5+1 magazine. 



The gun comes with a target grade Williams peep site, and an assortment of 10 different front site reticle inserts (circles and posts of different thicknesses). I was tired of using a scope. Wanted to go back to plinking with open sites. 



Reviews



“ - wow this thing will shoot! The last time I shot a gun that had this kind of accuracy was when I was a teen, and got to shoot a match-grade MCO Anschutz single shot that was worth close to $3000. Laying prone on the lawn, with no props or rests, a ten shot group was less than a dime at about 40feet. Went and got a proper .22 target and shot another 40 rounds at 20meters, this time laying on the ground, and using a bag of cracked corn as a rest. I managed to shoot three different 5 shot groups that were barely larger than a pea. The largest were a tad bigger than a nickle. Anyone looking for ultra accuracy at an affordable price, give this gun some thought. Tried Winchester, Remington, and Federal ammo. Best groups came from the Federal. I never played around with the Accutrigger setting, manual says states factory set at the lightest (around 2.5lbs) setting.” 



" I recently used this gun at boy scout camp while getting my rifle merit badge and I loved this gun. I had never used this type of sight before but it was great and at 50 feet with 5 shots it gave me a group that fit under a penny and connected all the holes together. I was so good with this gun that it even surprised the range master to see me get every target with it.”
